@ryches Yes, that complicates everything. Note that a network's source image and output mask can be different sizes. You can build a Unet with 5 encoders and 4 decoders. Then you can input images of size 700x1050 and output masks of size 350x525. 

So the question becomes what size input do we need so that the network has access to maximum information? If the answer is 700x1050, then we can use "train on crop, predict on full" technique with a 5 enc 4 dec Unet.

If the answer is that 350x525 contains maximum information, then I agree that there is no need for "train on crop, predict on full".

